explanation: This solution uses the sliding window technique with a hash table to keep track of the last seen index of each character. It maintains a left pointer and a right pointer, expanding the window to the right and shrinking it from the left when a duplicate is found. The time complexity is O(n) and the space complexity is O(1) as the hash table size is constant.

